00:54:15.930 --> 00:54:19.700
&gt;&gt; Clair Cuccio: Yes, so
mokuhanga is the Japanese term

00:54:19.700 --> 00:54:22.700
that means objectively

00:54:22.700 --> 00:54:27.220
and literally wood impression
picture, woodblock print.

00:54:27.220 --> 00:54:31.610
But it has been disseminated
from Japan today,

00:54:31.610 --> 00:54:36.610
in the last 20 years by a
group particularly interested

00:54:36.610 --> 00:54:40.350
in preserving the shokunin,
the artisan techniques

00:54:40.350 --> 00:54:43.180
through an approach of
sort of sending them

00:54:43.180 --> 00:54:46.960
out with the idea being
that there aren't that many,

00:54:46.960 --> 00:54:48.900
there is a limited
number of artisans,

00:54:48.900 --> 00:54:51.480
there are a limited number
of art students who in Japan

00:54:51.480 --> 00:54:53.290
who are interested in this mode.

00:54:53.290 --> 00:54:56.520
And so, if we let it
free we send it out,

00:54:56.520 --> 00:54:59.370
somewhat like ukiyo-e when
they migrated to Europe

00:54:59.370 --> 00:55:01.470
and they were sort of discovered
there and then they came back

00:55:01.470 --> 00:55:03.040
to Japan and Japan
realized oh wow,

00:55:03.040 --> 00:55:05.660
we do have something really
special here that we discounted

00:55:05.660 --> 00:55:08.720
as you know just popular art.

00:55:08.720 --> 00:55:11.910
This movement started to happen
with a small group of people,

00:55:11.910 --> 00:55:15.610
there are residencies there in
mokuhanga in woodblock prints

00:55:15.610 --> 00:55:19.120
that are based on these
traditional techniques

00:55:19.120 --> 00:55:22.140
with the idea being, not that
they stay the same, not the work

00:55:22.140 --> 00:55:23.440
of the artisan where
you're trying

00:55:23.440 --> 00:55:25.660
to reproduce the same
techniques, but to innovate

00:55:25.660 --> 00:55:27.780
and take the base of these
techniques and the base

00:55:27.780 --> 00:55:29.340
of these materials and
to create something new.

00:55:29.340 --> 00:55:32.490
And yes, there is
a greater movement,

00:55:32.490 --> 00:55:35.800
there's an American artist based
in New York, April Vollmer,

00:55:35.800 --> 00:55:38.260
if any of you are in the print
world you're probably familiar

00:55:38.260 --> 00:55:39.560
with her.

00:55:39.560 --> 00:55:44.200
She has a very active website,
